attacks.name: Seek Out
attacks.text: Search your deck for 1 card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Pull Away
attacks.text: If your opponent has 5 or more cards in his or her hand, your opponent discards a number of cards until your opponent has 4 cards left in his or her hand.

attacks.name: Mystic Fang
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Pokémon-ex, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

abilities.name: Intimidating Fang
abilities.text: As long as Mightyena is your Active Pokémon, any damage done to your Pokémon by an opponent's attack is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Shakedown
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

attacks.name: Overrun
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Bite Off
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Pokémon-ex, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage.

data.name: Mightyena

attacks.name: Hard Bite
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

data.flavorText: It will always obey the commands of a skilled Trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.

data.name: Mightyena δ
rules: This Pokémon is both Darkness Metal type.

attacks.name: Delta Fang
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Pokémon-ex, that Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Gang Up
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of Darkness Pokémon and Metal Pokémon you have in play.

attacks.name: Plunder
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Trainer cards attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dark Burst
attacks.text: If Sidney's Stadium is in play, this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

data.name: Team Aqua's Mightyena

attacks.name: Teampact
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Team Aqua Pokémon you have in play. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Thanks to Mightyena's outstanding leadership, it's very good at combination attacks that can leave a foe helpless.

data.name: Team Magma's Mightyena

attacks.name: Hostile Fang
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Team Aqua Pokémon, this attack does 40 more damage.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon is loyal to its master. It will protect its partner to the end, no matter what.

attacks.name: Aqua Call
attacks.text: Search your deck for Pokémon that has Team Aqua in its name, show up to 3 of them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

abilities.name: Call for Help
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Team Magma's Mightyena is your Active Pokémon, you may search your deck for a Pokémon with Team Magma in its name, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Team Magma's Mightyena is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage.

abilities.name: Cold Feet
abilities.text: If Mightyena is affected by a Special Condition, ignore all Energy necessary to use Mightyena's attacks.

attacks.name: Collude
attacks.text: If you played any Supporter card from your hand during this turn, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

attacks.name: Desperate Attack
attacks.text: If Mightyena has less Energy attached to it than the Defending Pokémon, this attack does 50 damage plus 30 more damage.

data.flavorText: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

data.name: Mightyena ex
rules: When Pokémon-ex has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Driving Howl
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon and switch it with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. Your opponent chooses the Benched Pokémon to switch. This power can't be used if Mightyena ex is affected by a Special Condition.
